==United Kingdom==
The health of children and youth in the UK is mainly the responsibility of the [[National Health Service|NHS]], for example child health screening [http://www.nsc.nhs.uk/ch_screen/child_ind.htm] and advice for parents of overweight children [http://www.nhsdirect.nhs.uk/articles/article.aspx?articleId=823]. School based services are therefore more limited than in the US.

