==History==
[[Inspection (medicine)|Medical inspection]] in schools was first instituted in [[France]] in 1886, then, in succession, this example was followed by [[Belgium]], [[Hungary]], [[Chile]], [[Germany]] and [[Great Britain]], the latter in 1908. In the United States, medical inspection in schools was first instituted in [[New York City]] in 1892, then in [[Boston]] in 1894, in [[Chicago]] in 1895, and in [[Philadelphia]] in 1898.<ref name="colliers"/>

